After making a fortune improving the design of oil drilling bits, Hughes becomes the Hollywood mogul behind RKO studios, and devotes his life to aviation. The film also depicts Hughes' romances Hollywood starlets Jean Harlow and Katharine Hepburn

programme.title: Empire

programme.title: Firewall

programme.title: The Hunted
programme.desc: A rogue special-forces soldier is tracked down by his former mentor in this action thriller starring Benicio del Toro stars as Aaron Hallam, one of the U.S. military's most skilled hand-to-hand combat operatives. In the years following his successful assassination of a Serbian warlord in late-'90s Kosovo, Hallam finds himself plagued by traumatic flashbacks of death and destruction, so much so that when he finally returns home, he regresses into a feral, survivalist state in the woods of the Pacific Northwest. There, he deliberately and elaborately hunts and kills poachers who happen to cross his path. When the FBI investigates the murders, they call in the man who taught Hallam everything he knows: retiree L.T. Bonham (Tommy Lee Jones). As the instructor pursues his unhinged former pupil, Bonham begins to learn about key events in Hallam's life that pushed him over the edge(n)

programme.title: Drag Me to Hell

Determined to get a promotion at work, Christine lays down the law when mysterious Mrs. Ganush literally begs for mercy at her feet. In retaliation, Mrs. Ganush places the curse of Lamia on her unfortunate target. programme.title: The Belko Experiment

programme.title: The Deer Hunter

programme.desc: Winner of five Academy Awards, Gladiator revived the sword and sandal epic while becoming one of the acclaimed and popular historical dramas of the decade! Russell Crowe won an Oscar for his star-making turn as a general whose family is murdered by a corrupt prince (Academy Award-nominee Joaquin Phoenix). He embarks on a desperate quest for revenge that sees him fighting in front of thousands of Romans in the Coliseum. Directed by acclaimed filmmaker Ridley Scott, Gladiator re-creates the glory of Ancient Rome with Academy Award-winning special effects. A modern classic. Starring Russell Crowe Joaquin Phoenix, Richard Harris, Connie Nielsen and Oliver Reed

programme.title: Mission
programme.desc: Brian De Palma directed this first instalment of the action thriller franchise that rebooted the American TV series (which ran from 1966 to 1973). Tom Cruise stars as agent Ethan Hunt, member of America's elite IMF team (that's the undercover spies of the Impossible Mission Force; not the financiers of the International Monetary Fund). Hunt and a group of colleagues are sent to Prague to both prevent a list of undercover agents' real identities from being disclosed, and to reveal who within the IMF has turned traitor. But things go disastrously wrong and all but one of the team are massacred. As the sole survivor, Hunt must now try to prove his innocence and discover the real betrayer before he is terminated by his own government. And thus begins a top-class, high-octane chase thriller, packed with jaw-dropping special effects and stunts

programme.title: Almost Famous
programme.desc: Written and directed by Cameron Crowe, Almost Famous tells the story of a 15-year-old boy who, in the early '70s, is given the opportunity to go on tour with a rock band. William Miller's mother is overly obsessed with drugs and the negative influence of rock on teenagers. But he is a music lover and his hobby is to write about bands for an underground newspaper. The boy's work eventually catches the attention of Lester Bangs (Philip Seymor Hoffman), editor of a rock magazine who then asks him to cover a great concert. William manages to get only an interview with the opening band, Stillwater, but even so he wins the admiration of another editor, this time, of Rolling Stone. Now the boy has the opportunity to continue traveling with Stillwater and write an article that could open up the way to showbiz. During the tour he meets various interesting people, including a girl he falls in love with (Kate Hudson). Crowe, who received an Oscar for Best Screenplay for this film, wrote the story based on his teenage experiences, when he also contributed to Rolling Stone(n)

programme.desc: Written and directed by Cameron Crowe, Almost Famous tells the story of a 15-year-old boy who, in the early '70s, is given the opportunity to go on tour with a rock band. William Miller's mother is overly obsessed with drugs and the negative influence of rock on teenagers. But he is a music lover and his hobby is to write about bands for an underground newspaper. The boy's work eventually catches the attention of Lester Bangs (Philip Seymor Hoffman), editor of a rock magazine who then asks him to cover a great concert. William manages to get only an interview with the opening band, Stillwater, but even so he wins the admiration of another editor, this time, of Rolling Stone. Now the boy has the opportunity to continue traveling with Stillwater and write an article that could open up the way to showbiz. During the tour he meets various interesting people, including a girl he falls in love with (Kate Hudson). Crowe, who received an Oscar for Best Screenplay for this film, wrote the story based on his teenage experiences, when he also contributed to Rolling Stone

programme.desc: Jorge Blanco's animation is as witty and family-friendly as you'd expect from a film that's written by Joe Stillman, who also wrote Shrek and Shrek 2. Astronaut Chuck Baker lands on Planet 51, expecting to plant a flag, hit a few golf balls and go home. of 1950s America, complete with a fascination with alien-invasion films. But this planet is inhabited by small, green aliens (is there any other kind?) whose society mirrors that The aliens are therefore terrified by their 'invader', just as he is by them. Only teenage astronomer Lem (Justin Long) appears unperturbed. He befriends Chuck and, in shades of ET, hides him in his home, before they embark on a journey to get Chuck back to his ship before it returns to Earth. There's plenty for kids and parents alike to enjoy in this affectionate dig at 50s society. Vocal talents include Gary Oldman, Seann William Scott, Jessica Biel and John Cleese(n)
